t: "So when you meet the disbelievers ňĻin battleňļ, strike ňĻtheirňļ necks until you have thoroughly subdued them, then bind them firmly. Later ňĻfree them either asňļ an act of grace or by ransom until the war comes to an end. So will it be. Had God willed, He ňĻHimselfňļ could have inflicted punishment on them. But He does ňĻthis only toňļ test some of you by means of others. And those who are martyred in the cause of God,¬†He will never render their deeds void"